---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const groupUrl = 'https://groups.google.com/g/watch-face-beta-testers';
const optInUrl = 'https://play.google.com/apps/testing/me.maxistar.voiceinbox';
const storeUrl = 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=me.maxistar.voiceinbox';
---
<Layout
  title="Join Android closed testing"
  description="How to join the Voice Inbox Google Play closed test, install the Android app, and provide useful feedback."
>
  <style>
    .intro {
      max-width: 820px;
    }
    .status {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      width: fit-content;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.24);
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 7px 12px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 850;
    }
    .status::before {
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--accent);
      content: '';
    }
    .lead {
      max-width: 760px;
      font-size: 1.12rem;
    }
    .summary {
      margin-top: 32px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 22px;
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .summary ul {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }
    .enrollment {
      display: grid;
      gap: 18px;
      margin-top: 24px;
      counter-reset: enrollment;
    }
    .step {
      position: relative;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 24px 24px 24px 76px;
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .step::before {
      position: absolute;
      top: 24px;
      left: 24px;
      display: grid;
      width: 34px;
      height: 34px;
      place-items: center;
      border-radius: 10px;
      color: #fff;
      background: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 900;
      counter-increment: enrollment;
      content: counter(enrollment);
    }
    .step h3 {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
    .step p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .account-note {
      margin-top: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .commitment {
      border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.28);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 24px;
      background: var(--accent-soft);
    }
    .commitment h2 {
      font-size: 1.45rem;
    }
    .checklist {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }
    .checklist li {
      position: relative;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 18px 18px 18px 48px;
      background: var(--surface);
    }
    .checklist li::before {
      position: absolute;
      top: 18px;
      left: 18px;
      display: grid;
      width: 20px;
      height: 20px;
      place-items: center;
      border: 2px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 6px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      content: '✓';
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 900;
    }
    .two-column {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 18px;
    }
    .two-column .card h2 {
      font-size: 1.45rem;
    }
    @media (max-width: 680px) {
      .step {
        padding: 70px 20px 20px;
      }
      .step::before {
        top: 20px;
        left: 20px;
      }
      .two-column {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <section class="intro">
    <span class="status">Android closed test</span>
    <p class="eyebrow">Help test Voice Inbox</p>
    <h1>Join the Google Play closed test.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Voice Inbox is not a public Google Play release yet. Follow all four steps below with the same
      Google account to become eligible, install the app, and help validate it on real Android devices.
    </p>
    <div class="summary">
      <strong>Before you start</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>An ARM64 device running Android 7.0 or later.</li>
        <li>About 704 MiB of free storage for speech-model installation.</li>
        <li>A suitable network connection for the normal model download, which is about 640 MiB.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Enrollment</p>
    <h2>Complete these steps in order.</h2>
    <div class="enrollment">
      <article class="step">
        <h3>Join the tester group</h3>
        <p>
          Join <a href={groupUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">watch-face-beta-testers on Google Groups</a>.
          Despite its name, this is the maintainer's shared beta-testing group for several applications,
          including Voice Inbox.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="step">
        <h3>Check your Google account</h3>
        <p>
          Make sure the account that joined the group is also the active account in Google Play on the
          Android device where you want to install Voice Inbox.
        </p>
        <p class="account-note">Using different accounts is the most common reason the test appears unavailable.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="step">
        <h3>Become a tester</h3>
        <p>
          Open the <a href={optInUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Voice Inbox testing opt-in page</a>
          and accept the invitation. Google may need a short time to update your access after you join the group.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="step">
        <h3>Install Voice Inbox</h3>
        <p>
          After opting in, open the <a href={storeUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Voice Inbox Google Play listing</a>
          and install or update the app. The listing remains restricted to eligible testers during the closed test.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section commitment">
    <p class="eyebrow">One important request</p>
    <h2>Please stay enrolled for at least 14 continuous days.</h2>
    <p>
      Google Play evaluates sustained closed-test participation. Please keep Voice Inbox installed or remain
      opted in and do not leave the testing program during this 14-day period. You do not need to use the app every day.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">What to test</p>
    <h2>A short, useful test pass</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Download the speech model, or install it from a compatible local model folder.</li>
      <li>Create a new output document or choose an existing <code>.txt</code> or <code>.md</code> file.</li>
      <li>Import an audio file and, if convenient, share a voice message to Voice Inbox from another app.</li>
      <li>Transcribe an audio task and confirm that text is appended to the output document.</li>
      <li>Leave and reopen Voice Inbox, then confirm that setup and task state are restored.</li>
      <li>Optionally select an audio folder and try the multi-file workflow.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="note">
      The normal model download needs network access. Once the model is installed, speech recognition runs locally on the device.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-column">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Send useful feedback</h2>
      <p>
        Use Google Play's private feedback option, or reply through the same channel where you received this invitation.
        If something fails, include your device model, Android version, what you expected, the steps that reproduced the issue,
        and a screenshot when relevant.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Cannot access the test?</h2>
      <p>Check that you joined the Google Group and that the same Google account is active in Google Play.</p>
      <p>
        Then reopen the <a href={optInUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">opt-in page</a> before the store listing.
        If access was just granted, wait a few minutes and try again. Availability can also depend on the current test rollout.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
